A total of 19 passengers have died, eight others injured at Changarawe in Mafinga Town, Iringa following the accident involving a truck and a minibus.

The vehicles involved in the tragedy were Scania with registration number T736 AAE and Coaster (T542 DQV).

Mafinga Town Hospital Medical Officer Dr Victor Msafiri confirmed to have received bodies of 19 people who succumbed in the deadly crash. Out of the 19 bodies, four have been identified by their relatives. He added that eight survivors are still receiving treatment at the facility and their health condition is improving.